'''DC内爆'''（英语：DC Implosion），是美国漫画出版商[[DC漫画|DC漫画]]在1978年将二十多个正在进行和计划进行的流行系列作品突然取消的事件。

==历史==
该名字是参考并讽刺“DC爆炸”，“DC爆炸”是DC漫画在一次市场营销活动中，开始出版更多的作品，而且所有的作品页面数上升，也导致价格上升。<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.dialbforblog.com/archives/252/publishorial.gif|title= Publishorial: Onward and Upward|first= Jenette|last= Kahn|authorlink= Jenette Kahn|date= September 1978|publisher= DC Comics|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140329065319/http://www.dialbforblog.com/archives/252/publishorial.gif|archivedate= 2014-03-29|deadurl= yes|access-date= 2016-03-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last= Daniels|first= Les|authorlink= Les Daniels|chapter= New Markets, New Formats: Comics Change With the Times|title= DC Comics: Sixty Years of the World's Favorite Comic Book Heroes|url= https://archive.org/details/dccomicssixtyyea0000dani|publisher= [[Little,_Brown_and_Company|Bulfinch Press]]|year= 1995|page= [https://archive.org/details/dccomicssixtyyea0000dani/page/178 178]|isbn= 0821220764|quote= The expansion was optimistically dubbed 'The DC Explosion'. Nothing seemed to work, however, and cutbacks were initiated that insiders ironically dubbed 'The DC Implosion'.}}</ref>DC爆炸首次在从1975年到1978年，一共出现57个新作品。“爆炸”一词首次亮相于1978年六月至九月的修整。<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.comicsbulletin.com/interviews/3621/cancelled-comics-cavalcade-30-years-later-with-paul-kupperberg/|title= ''Cancelled Comics Cavalcade'': 30 Years Later with Paul Kupperberg|first= Jim|last= Beard|date= July 26, 2007|publisher= [[Comics_Bulletin|Comics Bulletin]]|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140606234133/http://www.comicsbulletin.com/interviews/3621/cancelled-comics-cavalcade-30-years-later-with-paul-kupperberg/|archivedate= 2014年6月6日|deadurl= yes|accessdate= 2016年3月1日}}</ref>

自20世纪70年代初，DC看到了漫威漫画成为市场的主导地位，部分原因是漫威漫画明显增加它出版的作品（包括原材料和转载的书籍）的数量。在很大程度上，DC爆炸是为了超越漫威漫画。

DC在1977年冬季经历持续滞销，部分原因为北美1977年和1978年的暴风雪，暴风雪破坏了分销和削弱消费者的购买力。<ref name="DialB1">{{cite web|url= http://www.dialbforblog.com/archives/252/|title= Secret Origins of the DC Implosion Part One|first= Kirk|last= Kimball|date= n.d.|publisher= Dial "B" For Blog|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131222080959/http://www.dialbforblog.com/archives/252/|archivedate= 2013-12-22|deadurl= yes|accessdate= 2016-03-01}}</ref>此外，影响经济的通货膨胀，经济衰退，和整个漫画产业的纸张和印刷费用提高降低了盈利，还有读者数量的持续下降。对此，公司高层下令取消几个仍处于开发阶段的新系列作品。<ref name="DialB1" /><ref>{{cite web|url= http://bobrozakis.blogspot.com/2012/11/bobro-archives-dc-implosion.html|title= BobRo Archives: The DC Implosion|first= Bob|last= Rozakis|authorlink= Bob Rozakis|date= November 30, 2012|publisher= BobRozakis.blogspot.com|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140804015718/http://bobrozakis.blogspot.com/2012/11/bobro-archives-dc-implosion.html|archivedate= 2014-08-04|deadurl= no|quote= The Warner Publishing powers-that-be told Kahn and company President Sol Harrison to cancel the plans for bigger books and cut the line to 20 32-page titles at 40c each.|accessdate= 2016-03-01}}</ref>在这些会议上，会议决定，DC长期的旗舰作品《侦探漫画》在＃480结束，后该决定因办公室内的剧烈争吵而被推翻，《侦探漫画》没有与销售较好的《Batman Family》合并。<ref>{{cite web|url= http://goodcomics.comicbookresources.com/2012/07/27/comic-book-legends-revealed-377/|title= Comic Book Legends Revealed #377|first= Brian|last= Cronin|date= July 27, 2012|publisher= [[Comic_Book_Resources|Comic Book Resources]]|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140409130442/http://goodcomics.comicbookresources.com/2012/07/27/comic-book-legends-revealed-377/|archivedate= 2014-04-09|deadurl= no|accessdate= 2016-03-01}}</ref>

在1978年6月22日，DC漫画宣布裁员，40％的订单被取消。编辑阿尔米格罗姆<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.wtv-zone.com/silverager/interviews/milgrom_1.shtml|title= Al Milgrom Interview|first= Bryan D.|last= Stroud|date= April 7, 2010|publisher= The Silver Age Lantern|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120901223734/http://www.wtv-zone.com/silverager/interviews/milgrom_1.shtml|archivedate= 2012-09-01|deadurl= no|accessdate= 2016-03-01}}</ref>和拉里·哈马的两个员工被解雇。<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.nycgraphicnovelists.com/2010/01/larry-hama-all-about-character.html|title= Larry Hama: All About Character|first= Christopher|last= Irving|date= January 19, 2010|publisher= NYC Graphic Novelists|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131221190740/http://www.nycgraphicnovelists.com/2010/01/larry-hama-all-about-character.html|archivedate= 2013-12-21|deadurl= yes|quote= By that time, me and Al Milgrom had gotten imploded out of DC in what they called 'The Great Implosion'.|access-date= 2016-03-01}}</ref>


==《Cancelled Comic Cavalcade》==

大約有三十個標題未發表的作品都出現在《Cancelled Comic Cavalcade》中，這是1978年夏季的兩期“ashcan”系列，僅僅為了確立公司版權而“發布”了有限數量的作品。<ref name="DialB1"/><ref>{{cite web|url= http://lsh.0catch.com/ccc/cccintro.htm|title= ''Cancelled Comic Cavalcade'': Introduction|date= Summer 1978|publisher= DC Comics|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140424202333/http://lsh.0catch.com/ccc/cccintro.htm|archivedate= 2014-04-24|deadurl= yes|quote= "Just to make it official – ''Cancelled Comic Cavalcade'', Vol. 1, No. 1, Summer 1978, DC Comics, Inc.|access-date= 2019-07-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=McAvennie|first= Michael|last2=Dolan|first2=Hannah, ed.|chapter= 1970s|title = DC Comics Year By Year: A Visual Chronicle|publisher=[[Dorling_Kindersley|Dorling Kindersley]] |year=2010|location= London, United Kingdom|isbn= 978-0-7566-6742-9 |page= 179 |quote =  With the devastating ''DC Implosion'', a majority of the thirty-one titles terminated in 1978 were canceled in the middle of storylines. Therefore, staff members "published", in extremely limited quantities, two volumes of ''Cancelled Comic Cavalcade''.}}</ref> 這個頭銜是DC 20世紀40年代系列Comic Cavalcade的劇本。已經為取消的出版物製作的一些材料後來用於其他系列。這兩卷由一些故事和早期的庫存故事組成，由DC工作人員以黑白方式印在辦公室複印機上。每卷共製作了35份，並分發給該材料的創作者，美國版權局和Overstreet漫畫書價格指南作為其存在的證據。被認為是一個有價值的收藏品，2011年版的漫畫書價格指南中，這兩個問題的價值高達3,680美元。

內容從完成的故事到不完整的藝術作品。封面上有新的插圖;第一個顯示被取消的書籍英雄無論是昏迷還是死在地上，第二個顯示被取消的英雄被戴著西裝的戴著眼鏡的男子踢出辦公室。第一期的封面價格為10美分<ref>''Cancelled Comic Cavalcade'' #1 (Summer 1978)</ref> ，while the second carried a cover price of $1.00,而第二期的封面價格為1.00美元<ref> ''Cancelled Comic Cavalcade'' #2 (Fall 1978)</ref>，但該出版物實際上從未出售過。

